title: For Sale:  Burris AR-332 Prism Sight 3x with Quick Detach mount
postcontent:
Selling my Burris AR-332 Prism Sight with 3x magnification.  Includes lighted reticle with red or green illumination, and 5 brightness settings, all on one easy knob.  Turn to Off position for unlit black reticle.  Reticle is a CQ close quarters donut design, and includes range and bullet drop estimation.  Eye relief is just right for most AR-15 style rifles.  The view is best for ranges of 10 to 200 yards.

Unit is lightly used and works perfectly.  No scratches on the optical surfaces, and the body still looks brand new as well.  Includes battery, sunshade, integrated covers, and Burris AR-QD Quick Detach mount.  Comes with everything you need to use it today on your rifle, as long as you have a little bit of empty Picatinny rail.  

Sight plus mount sell for $438 total on Midway.  I'm asking $330 for mine.  Cash only, pickup only, in northern burbs area (glenview/northbrook).

Oh, and to those people who think the reticle in these sights is canted to the side:  it's an illusion.  It's the slope of the prism - that's how they work.  To be sure, switch the rifle to your left shoulder and look through it with your left eye.  If you thought it was canted before, it should appear canted the opposite way now.  It makes no difference anyway.  I shot tight groups with this sight at 75 yd.
